{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:genesis.25",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "genesis",
    "chapterNumber": 25,
    "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25",
    "summary": "Source text for Genesis 25 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:1",
      "text": "Abraham took another wife, whose name was Keturah.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:2",
      "text": "She bore him Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:3",
      "text": "Jokshan was the father of Sheba and Dedan. The sons of Dedan were Asshurim, Letushim, and Le-ummim.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:4",
      "text": "The sons of Midian were Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida, and Eldaah. All these were the children of Keturah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:5",
      "text": "Abraham gave all he had to Isaac.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:6",
      "text": "But to the sons of his concubines Abraham gave gifts, and while he was still living he sent them away from his son Isaac, eastward to the east country.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:7",
      "text": "These are the days of the years of Abraham's life, a hundred and seventy-five years.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:8",
      "text": "Abraham breathed his last and died in a good old age, an old man and full of years, and was gathered to his people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:9",
      "text": "Isaac and Ishmael his sons buried him in the cave of Mach-pelah, in the field of Ephron the son of Zohar the Hittite, east of Mamre,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:10",
      "text": "the field which Abraham purchased from the Hittites. There Abraham was buried, with Sarah his wife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:11",
      "text": "After the death of Abraham God blessed Isaac his son. And Isaac dwelt at Beer-lahai-roi.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:12",
      "text": "These are the descendants of Ishmael, Abraham's son, whom Hagar the Egyptian, Sarah's maid, bore to Abraham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:13",
      "text": "These are the names of the sons of Ishmael, named in the order of their birth: Nebaioth, the first-born of Ishmael; and Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:14",
      "text": "Mishma, Dumah, Massa,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:15",
      "text": "Hadad, Tema, Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:16",
      "text": "These are the sons of Ishmael and these are their names, by their villages and by their encampments, twelve princes according to their tribes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:17",
      "text": "(These are the years of the life of Ishmael, a hundred and thirty-seven years; he breathed his last and died, and was gathered to his kindred.)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:18",
      "text": "They dwelt from Havilah to Shur, which is opposite Egypt in the direction of Assyria; he settled over against all his people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:19",
      "text": "These are the descendants of Isaac, Abraham's son: Abraham was the father of Isaac,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:20",
      "text": "and Isaac was forty years old when he took to wife Rebekah, the daughter of Bethuel the Aramean of Paddan-aram, the sister of Laban the Aramean.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:21",
      "text": "And Isaac prayed to the Lord for his wife, because she was barren; and the Lord granted his prayer, and Rebekah his wife conceived.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:22",
      "text": "The children struggled together within her; and she said, “If it is thus, why do I live?” So she went to inquire of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:23",
      "text": "And the Lord said to her, “Two nations are in your womb, and two peoples, born of you, shall be divided; the one shall be stronger than the other, the elder shall serve the younger.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:24",
      "text": "When her days to be delivered were fulfilled, behold, there were twins in her womb.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:25",
      "text": "The first came forth red, all his body like a hairy mantle; so they called his name Esau.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:26",
      "text": "Afterward his brother came forth, and his hand had taken hold of Esau's heel; so his name was called Jacob. Isaac was sixty years old when she bore them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:27",
      "text": "When the boys grew up, Esau was a skilful hunter, a man of the field, while Jacob was a quiet man, dwelling in tents.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:28",
      "text": "Isaac loved Esau, because he ate of his game; but Rebekah loved Jacob.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:29",
      "text": "Once when Jacob was boiling pottage, Esau came in from the field, and he was famished.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:30",
      "text": "And Esau said to Jacob, “Let me eat some of that red pottage, for I am famished!” (Therefore his name was called Edom.)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:31",
      "text": "Jacob said, “First sell me your birthright.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:32",
      "text": "Esau said, “I am about to die; of what use is a birthright to me?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:33",
      "text": "Jacob said, “Swear to me first.” So he swore to him, and sold his birthright to Jacob.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.25.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 25:34",
      "text": "Then Jacob gave Esau bread and pottage of lentils, and he ate and drank, and rose and went his way. Thus Esau despised his birthright.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
